      "side": 1,
      "message": "File: ClientHttp1Session.java:55 and ClientHttp2Session.java:38\n  Issue: synchronized intrinsic lock on a concurrent collection is an anti-pattern. Locking on the collection object itself is confusing when the collection is\n    ConcurrentLinkedQueue/ConcurrentHashMap (which has its own internal locks). Future maintainers will be unsure which lock to acquire.\n  Severity: Moderate\n  Recommendation: Use a dedicated private final Object lock \u003d new Object(); (or a ReentrantLock) and document it clearly.",
      "revId": "10e1de33a5f3b035eb140121344ec336a0b9ff84",
      "serverId": "7fc14799-209e-464c-9743-7a06c2c21a81"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": false,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "f464e2e2_1aa3a170",
        "filename": "protocol/restconf-client/src/main/java/org/opendaylight/restconf/client/impl/ClientHttp1Session.java",
        "patchSetId": 14
