        "id": 9229
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-05-19T14:16:34Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I will reply to all comments on this class here.\nI looked into fixing this with ReentrantLock blocks to \"do not hold locks over I/O\". However, I realized that if we drop the lock before firing writeAndFlush(), we introduce a severe race condition for HTTP/1.1 pipelining: Thread B could be faster than Thread A, writing the requests out of order, which would cause us to map the server\u0027s responses to the wrong callbacks.\nFixing that with locks woud require multiple locks and also another queue for write to maintain order.\ninstead I tried to limit it to netty event loop\nchannelRead0 and channelInactive already run on it.\n\nI was already trying to do that here: https://git.opendaylight.org/gerrit/c/netconf/+/122680/comment/e003df1f_51c89f28/\nand to address that comment I added check if channel is still active.\nThen it was about datatype of queue variable, but now it is done to resolve reported issues and it is much simplier than with locks.\n\nLike this we ensure correct order without locking on synchronization.\n\ncomments also mention ClientHttp2Session, that is reworked in following patch and after that this issues are not present anymore, so I hope it is ok to left it like it is in this patch",
      "parentUuid": "48c5b841_57ad2a53",
      "revId": "10e1de33a5f3b035eb140121344ec336a0b9ff84",
      "serverId": "7fc14799-209e-464c-9743-7a06c2c21a81"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "6dbe02d0_eef50163",
        "filename": "protocol/restconf-client/src/main/java/org/opendaylight/restconf/client/impl/ClientHttp1Session.java",
