      "writtenOn": "2026-05-19T10:50:40Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "File: ClientHttp1Session.java:61-69 and ClientHttp2Session.java:51-64\n  Issue: Holding a lock over I/O. channel.writeAndFlush() is called while holding synchronized(queue) / synchronized(map). Flushing can involve network I/O and Netty\n    futures. Holding a monitor lock here blocks other threads from accessing the collection for the entire write duration, hurts throughput, and may cause a deadlock if\n\n    a Netty callback tries to acquire the same lock synchronously.\n  Severity: Major\n  Recommendation: Move writeAndFlush() outside the lock (see the incomplete-synchronization fix above — if you drop synchronized entirely this goes away naturally).",
      "revId": "10e1de33a5f3b035eb140121344ec336a0b9ff84",
      "serverId": "7fc14799-209e-464c-9743-7a06c2c21a81"
